. . no, what do you call them . . . "},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2202.942","u": "Cotton . . . "},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2203.698","u": "Not cotton, such smocks."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2206.902","u": "Oh smocks."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2207.710","u": "They gave us such mantles. No stockings. If one would get stockings&#226;one was yellow and one black. And when we arrived we looked so terrible, that when the foremen from the Messerschmidt factory arrived to look us over and to take some of us for work, they openly stated: &#39;That is an outrage.&#39; And then we came to Burgau. In Burgau were to be five hundred persons. But they sent in another transport. So there were a thousand women. And it started&#226;spotted fever typhus. Very many women died from spotted fever. The Hungarian Jewesses suffered most, from spotted fever and from diarrhea. The lice were so spread out that one could not stand it. Then I came down with spotted fever, and with . . . and it commenced with my legs. I was unable to get up any more. From Burgau we were sent to Kirkheim."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2275.022","u": "And how did they send you? You . . . "},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2276.250","u": "I was carried. The prisoners carried me, to Kirkheim. And from Kirkheim . . . I was completely sick, the legs were already black, so I was sent to the lager-revier, lager four, near Landsberg. The famous lager-revier in which thousands, more than thousands of people have died from spotted fever."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2298.553","u": "That is not very far from here."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2299.731","u": "No, not far, Landsberg. There I already . . . there it started already to fester&#226;and they could not help me any more. The physicians came of course. They told me nothing, but I saw it was the end. Then evacuation from the lager. Whoever could still walk was chased away. I of course could not get up anymore. The first . . . the SS came and brought a horse cart. I told him then &#39;shoot me.&#39; So he said: &#39;no child, now you will live, it is I who will be hanged.&#39;"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2332.686","u": "Why, did he know already."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2334.253","u": "[laughter in her voice] He know already that the Americans are approaching. And there . . . it is interesting about the SS. If somebody comes forward and pleads to die, then you must live. But if you wish to live&#226;then you must die."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2345.668","u": "Nu."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2346.457","u": "And because I told him with complete indifference that I wish to die&#226;then he says&#226;you must live. Then I was taken again to another lager, lager one, and in lager one I was liberated by the Americans. The last day before liberation,&#226;the SS had run away, and we remained. The front passed through our lager. On one side were the Germans, on the other the Americans. And they were shooting at each other. Those who could get out, got out. I had to lie there. Then by accident the barracks of the SS caught fire, which stood nearby. And I thought then that the barracks were set on fire by us. Everybody who could still drag his legs, ran out. I did not know what to do, because such a death in . . . "},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2393.608","u": " . . . fire."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2393.955","u": " . . . in fire I did not want. Then I threw off all the blankets, and threw myself down . . . from the plankbed. And so I slid out."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2401.716","u": "Was it a high plankbed or a low one?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2403.223","u": "These were such earth barracks . . . "},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2405.938","u": "Yes, what kind?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2407.283","u": " . . . built into ground, very deep in the ground . . . "},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2410.028","u": "Oh."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2410.295","u": "Like for dogs. And then, it was after the rain, I slid out, and it was after the rain. I did not have a good bandage, but only a paper dressing, and the . . . dirt and all that got in [into the wounds] and then everything came to an end and went kaput."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2425.929","u": "Nu."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2426.486","u": "Two days after liberation the Americans took me to a German hospital, and physicians said, I will live only ten days. But I told them that I will stand ten operations. And I did stand it. However due to the beating that I got, as well as from lying&#226;that spot was not completely [searches for words] nu . . . "},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2449.785","u": "Not completely healed?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2450.751","u": " . . . was not healed, and due to the lying it became irritated, and I developed a decubitus, and a hole [was formed] and still today the scar is that big. And I got through three operations. I got through three amputations."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2463.330","u": "What do you say, a decubitus?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2465.077","u": "Decubitus, that is the scar, here such . . . "},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2467.031","u": "Go on. Did they operate under chloroform?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2470.833","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2471.601","u": "Nu."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2472.160","u": "And the physicians predicted that I will die in ten days."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2474.916","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2475.440","u": "I had thirty two kilos after liberation [weighed thirty two kilograms]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2478.138","u": "How much do you weigh now?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2479.244","u": "Now? [laughter] Approximately over sixty. My height is one meter, sixty four [cm]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2481.817","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2482.274","u": "And I had thrity-two and in spite of that I pulled through. After liberation still very many died. From diarrhea. Because they started eating. It was terrible. People saw food for the first time [smiling]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2495.645","u": "In what lager was that, in Landsberg?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2499.004","u": "That was in the lager, I was in lager one at the end."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2502.527","u": "But you were in the hospital in Landsberg?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2503.992","u": "No, no. First I was in Holzhausen. There they cared for me very well. And from Holzhausen&#226;to Landsberg to Schwaben [??] in Munich."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2514.318","u": " . . . the lower leg, twenty centimeters below the knee. Right here, touch it."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2522.668","u": "Yes. Twenty centimeters under the knee. Now."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2524.303","u": "That is called lower leg amputation."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2526.597","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2527.054","u": " . . . both are lost."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2528.568","u": "And . . . "},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2529.196","u": "And now I walk very well. In spite of the fact that the Germans said I won&#39;t be able to walk."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2533.515","u": "And what are you doing here at the university?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2535.222","u": "I study pharmacy."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2536.807","u": "Yes. And how are things here?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2539.280","u": "I am very satisfied with the university. The professors are very good to us, and they are so friendly. The relations between professors and students is so great, that indeed one could not find it at any other university."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2551.151","u": "And how do the students get along?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2552.828","u": "Very well. It is interesting. One was able to see that it is possible to live together. And when man lives with man then nationality plays no part. What matters is the person not the nationality."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2562.477","u": "Have you relatives in America?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2564.052","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2564.559","u": "Do they write to you?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2565.884","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2566.274","u": "Where do they live?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2567.120","u": "In Chicago. I received affidavits from Chicago."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2569.595","u": "I am from Chicago, could I look them up?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2571.531","u": "[laughing] Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2571.961","u": "What is their name?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2572.678","u": "[cheerfully] La Salle Street . . . Helberg"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2575.480","u": "Write down their address."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2576.169","u": "I bring it right away."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2577.117","u": "What is their name?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2578.744","u": "Helberg."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2579.940","u": "Helberg. The first name?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2581.441","u": "Charles Helberg."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2582.549","u": "What?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2583.038","u": "Charl Helberg."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2584.316","u": "Charl?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2584.783","u": "Charles."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2585.562","u": "And that is an office on La Salle street."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2587.935","u": "What is his profession?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2592.842","u": "I don&#39;t know anything about that."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2591.387","u": "Yes. Is it his office?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2592.842","u": "I don&#39;t know."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2593.479","u": "What number on La Salle."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2594.235","u": "La Salle, North, 224."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2596.611","u": "225?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2597.377","u": "24."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2598.365","u": "224, La Salle, North."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2599.102","u": "North La Salle Street."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2601.286","u": "Now I shall see that man in two weeks."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2604.398","u": "Yes, that will be very . . . "},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2604.925","u": "I shall transmit regards from you."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2605.811","u": "You may tell that I have received the affidavit."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2610.034","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2610.650","u": "But I must wait for the quota. And &#34;two legs&#34; are not enough to get any preference."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2615.966","u": "How long . . . under quota do you come? The Polish?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2619.080","u": "On the Polish quota, and it is filled. Probably I have still to wait a year. And if by then UNNRA is out of existence then I have nothing to . . . "},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2625.345","u": "Oh, we&#39;ll arrange that with the Nias. I myself will take care of it."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2628.516","u": "[with friendly and somewhat skeptical laughter] Ya, they told me there that the quota [she means waiting list] is very large and that I can&#39;t get over."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2633.720","u": "And the name is Charles Helberg."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2635.946","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2636.114","u": "You don&#39;t know what his business is."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2636.942","u": "No."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2637.404","u": "What is he to you?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2638.747","u": "He is the uncle of my mother. But he was interested very much from the beginning, but he is unable to do [much] and . . . "},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2645.212","u": "What do you mean&#226;unable, no money?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2646.727","u": "No, it is not the money. But besides what can that help me [her voice fades, she mumbles]."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2650.817","u": "You have what."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2651.943","u": "[disconcerted] here I have nothing. I am maintained by UNRRA but . . . "},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2655.514","u": "Does he send you packages?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2656.789","u": "No, because he can&#39;t send. Because they sent me a few times, [but] I did not receive them."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2665.404","u": "Hm. Now is that all that you want to tell us?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2667.428","u": "Yes that is all that I want . . . "},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2668.594","u": "What do you want to tell to the American students. [laughingly] "},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2670.468","u": "[also laughingly] To tell the students?&#226;I want to say we have learned very much. Still we are not pessimists. That is we have come to learn . . . "},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2678.529","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2678.816","u": " . . . that there is only one reality. The reality of the Evil. But in spite of that we are not pessimists. We have also learned that the potentiality of the human soul is very great. One can stand very much [laughter]. And that is told by a human being who runs around on false limbs. Life is more interesting than death, possibly not easier."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2698.540","u": "How old are you?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2699.469","u": "Thirty."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2701.962","u": "I shall look up that man. Charles Helberger?"},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2704.327","u": "Helberg."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2705.076","u": "Hellberg, 224 North La Salle Street."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2708.644","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2709.094","u": "Chicago. And you don&#39;t know his occupation."},    {"who": "Roma Tcharnabroda", "start": "2711.160","u": "No."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2711.657","u": "[In English] This concludes the most interesting spool, number 155 at the UNRRA University. [Pause. Knocking sound.] These knocks are the knocks of the artificial legs of the young girl, who just talked to me, and she is now leaving the room."}        ]
    }
_jsready = true;
var return_val;
switch (String(type)){
        case "transcription":
        return_val = transcription.interview;
        break;
            case "english_translation":
        return_val = english_translation.interview;
        break;
    }
return return_val;
}
function js_ready(){
    return _jsready;
}
